<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> -I don't understand this, we all pay the same amount to play, we all experience the game the way we enjoy it, so <br>
10. WHY!!!! are the people who run RTA telling the server how and when to play?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Im assuming you not familiar with the way RTA runs, which is cool. Theres nobody in charge, accept ourselves. Its a skewed version of democracy. Each guild fullfills the requirements (certain amount of planable toons), then is allowed into the committee, so to speak. The guild assigns its own reps, and those reps speak for the guild. Then ALL the reps from ALL the guilds collaborate to keep the Rathe civil. In this case, there is no president. So, I dont see where you think there is dictatorship, or corruption.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 11. Is the Rathe made up of a bunch of children who need direction and guidance from other children?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Sadly, yes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 12. Why do we have a rotation calendar? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Because if we didnt, people would have /guildwar assigned to a hotkey. There would be constant fighting over planes, epic mobs, dragons, etc. and nothing would ever get killed. 5 guilds would show up in Hate at the same time, and all get wiped out while wondering why 4 other guilds are there.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 13. Why do we have to sign up and why are there rules?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Why are there rules? As opposed to....what..NOT having rules?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 14. Why do I need permission to go to the planes?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
