<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Then to have whining little babies come running to the RTA/Flame board, just so they can bash someone for playing the game by the game rules?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Hmm....Its funny you see it this way: &quot;RTA rules are a dictatorship, and unjust, but the games rules ARE fair.&quot;<br>
<br>
Heres the thing, the way the GMs run the game, IS fair, but its not JUST. The RTA is the Rathes attempt to correct those problems on a gentlemans agreement basis. Beleive it or not, the game would not be much fun if everyone was warring over everything. If that was the case, there WOULD be dictator guilds saying things like &quot;Hmmm...52 weeks from now, you can have Ragefire. Hes ours until then.&quot; simply because they can. One guild would always come out on top.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 17. Why is my guild not allowed to bring more then 6 people from another posting entity guild to my raid?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
