I think it has something to do with cheating about the number of planable toons your guild has, and more than 6 people would constitute a sharing of a plane. To be honest, the rule is overlooked, with the exception of specific mobs that MUST be taken down by your guild ALONE to get on rotation, proving that your guild is powerful enough to do it alone.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 18. Who makes up all these rules?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
We do. If every rep agreed, we could do away with the above rule. not that we ever would.<br>
<br>
